  <prompt>
    Migrate frontend Pattern B name-resolve consumers from literal-name fetches to stable-ID fetches. Affected sites: `useAiSummary.ts:285` (code-pages hook calling `/by-name/`) + `DocumentEmailWizard.tsx:628` (SpaarkeAi solution wizard step). Each call site changes from `/api/ai/playbooks/by-name/{name}` to `/api/ai/playbooks/by-id/{id}`. Per FR-03 acceptance, post-migration the by-name endpoint sees zero calls from production code.

    **Refresh (Q&A 2026-06-22 Q1)**: Stable lookups go through `sprk_playbookid` (immutable opaque ID, GUID-format). The endpoint route is `/api/ai/playbooks/by-id/{id}` (NOT `/by-id/{id}`). See spec.md § Canonical Field Naming for the corrected role table.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform frontend developer. Expert in React 18 hooks + SpaarkeAi solution + PCF/code-page Spaarke Auth patterns.</role>

  <goal>
    `useAiSummary.ts:285` and `DocumentEmailWizard.tsx:628` call `/api/ai/playbooks/by-id/{id}` with the appropriate stable code. Literal playbook-name strings are removed from the call sites (kebab-case codes inlined or hoisted to a shared constant module). Vitest unit tests + a UI smoke test confirm the summary/wizard flow still works end-to-end.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-03 + §1.7 Pattern B (frontend variant). `useAiSummary.ts:285` is the React hook used by code-pages for AI summary; `DocumentEmailWizard.tsx:628` is the workspace wizard's playbook-trigger step. Both currently hit `/by-name/`. After migration, they hit `/by-code/`. The codes table from spec §1.7.3 supplies the target codes.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/code-pages/AnalysisWorkspace/src/hooks/useAiSummary.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/DocumentEmailWizard/DocumentEmailWizard.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/services/ (potential shared client for AI lookups)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">Frontend handles 404 ProblemDetails shape from `/by-code/` (per task 011); display user-friendly error when code missing.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Frontend logging — no message content / file content / memory facts in client telemetry.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Dark-mode compatibility preserved for any UI changes (none expected, but verify).</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-03 acceptance: zero `/by-name/` calls from these two files post-migration.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">NFR-07 not directly applicable (these are not pre-fill flows); preserve existing UX behavior (loading states, error handling).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">DO NOT modify backend `/by-name/` endpoint (task 024 owns deprecation telemetry).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Use `npm install --legacy-peer-deps --no-audit --no-fund` for any solution rebuilds (NOT `npm ci`).</constraint>
  </constraints>

